<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-03T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-03T19:00:00-05:00" n="572" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d572">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/206</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Gonzales</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-03T19:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 3, 1917, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Francisco Sugar Company fear for safety of property sugar estate
                            Francisco at Guayabal, Cuba, and lives of employees.</p>
                        <p>You will request of Cuban Government its proper protection of this
                            plantation. Owners state that up to now absolutely no protection has
                            been afforded by the Cuban authorities, horses and stores having been
                            stolen by the insurgents.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>